summary: Technology leader with 10+ years of software engineering experience, and over 5 years of technical management experience (including 2nd-level management).   I lead teams of machine learning engineers at Seldon Technologies, focusing on the scalability and performance our Open Source & Enterprise products. With over 5M installations, Seldon Core is the most popular open source framework for ML deployment, and enables users to orchestrate thousands of production machine learning models with advanced monitoring, programmatic governance, explainability workflows and outlier detection capabilities.   Concurrently, I lead multiple research initiatives at The Institute for Ethical AI and Machine Learning, which revolve primarily around algorithmic bias, adversarial robustness and privacy preserving machine learning. I manage the research & development functions at the institute, including our open source frameworks, our university partnerships, and our core contributions to the IEEE, ISO, ACM the European Commission and the Linux Foundation.  I am a lead maintainer for a several open source projects that are exploring different aspects of the end-to-end monitoring and production machine learning lifecycle, some of these include Seldon Core (https://github.com/SeldonIO/seldon-core/), Kubeflow KFServing (https://github.com/kubeflow/kfserving/), ExplainableAI Toolkit (https://github.com/EthicalML/xai), Vulkan Kompute (https://github.com/EthicalML/vulkan-kompute), ML Tool Ecosystem (https://github.com/EthicalML/awesome-production-machine-learning/) and a couple of other non-technical projects such as our current announcement of the Linux Foundation Trusted AI Principles (https://lfaidata.foundation/blog/2021/02/08/lf-ai-data-announces-principles-for-trusted-ai/) and the Production Monitoring Patterns (https://towardsdatascience.com/production-machine-learning-monitoring-outliers-drift-explainers-statistical-performance-d9b1d02ac158).
